{"id":"meshelemiah","term":"Meshelemiah","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Friendship of Jehovah, a Levite of the family of the Korhites, called also Shelemiah (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 9:21\">1 Chr. 9:21</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 26:1\">26:1</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 26:2\">2</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 26:9\">9</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 26:14\">14</a>). He was a temple gate-keeper in the time of David.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Chronicles 9:21","1 Chronicles 26:1","1 Chronicles 26:2","1 Chronicles 26:9","1 Chronicles 26:14"]}